# LockIn schedule-update — credentials TEMPLATE.
#
#   cp credentials.env.example credentials.env
#   # then fill in the real password below.
#
# `credentials.env` is gitignored and MUST NEVER be committed. To use this skill
# in another environment (or with a Codex agent), either copy a filled-in
# credentials.env there, or set SUPABASE_DB_PASSWORD / LOCKIN_DATABASE_URL as a
# secret in that environment instead of using this file.

# --- Pick ONE of the two ways to supply the password ---

# Option A — full connection URL (password included):
# LOCKIN_DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres.hwrnevicgtnbexnsxitm:REPLACE_WITH_PASSWORD@aws-1-us-west-2.pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres?sslmode=require

# Option B — just the password (connection coordinates default to LockIn prod):
# SUPABASE_DB_PASSWORD=REPLACE_WITH_PASSWORD

# --- Optional: override coordinates for a different database (defaults shown) ---
# LOCKIN_DB_HOST=aws-1-us-west-2.pooler.supabase.com
# LOCKIN_DB_PORT=5432
# LOCKIN_DB_USER=postgres.hwrnevicgtnbexnsxitm
# LOCKIN_DB_NAME=postgres
# PSQL_BIN=/opt/homebrew/opt/libpq/bin/psql
